TITLE: 3 Americans sentenced to death after failed Congo coup plot sent home
SUMMARY: The repatriation came amid efforts by Congolese authorities to sign a minerals deal with the U.S. in exchange for security support to fight rebels in the country’s conflict-hit east

TITLE: 20 killed in fire at nursing home in northern China
SUMMARY: China’s official Xinhua news agency said Wednesday the fire started Tuesday night in northern Hebei province. Six hours later, 20 people were confirmed dead

TITLE: IMF reaches $20 billion bailout deal with troubled Argentina
SUMMARY: The preliminary agreement will provide a welcome reprieve to President Javier Milei as he seeks to overturn the country’s old economic order

TITLE: Protesters rally for the fourth week against Hungary’s law banning LGBTQ Pride events
SUMMARY: The legislation prohibits events depicting homosexuality to those under the age of 18 and has drawn comparisons to Russia’s anti-LGBTQ policies

TITLE: Global pharma shares plunge as Trump doubles down on tariff threat
SUMMARY: Pharmaceutical imports were initially exempt from Trump’s first set of reciprocal tariffs last week but his administration has since indicated that levies on the sector are coming

TITLE: Trump's sweeping new global tariffs take effect
SUMMARY: Trump said the pause will apply to more than 75 countries, but not China. Tariffs on Chinese goods will now rise to 125

TITLE: King Charles and Queen Camilla met with pope
SUMMARY: The meeting comes weeks after the 88-year-old pontiff's weekslong hospitalization

TITLE: Trump suddenly backs off global tariff plan after days of economic and market turmoil
SUMMARY: The president paused higher import duties for dozens of countries for 90 days but hiked levies on China to 125

TITLE: The U.S. and China are copying each other, giving rise to memes and mockery
SUMMARY: As President Donald Trump tries to return the U.S. to its manufacturing past, China wants to make its economy more like that of the U.S. by boosting domestic consumption

TITLE: An unimaginable tragedy at a celebrity-studded nightclub plunges Dominican Republic into mourning
SUMMARY: Celebrities, officials and Dominicans from the U.S. were among the hundreds who went to see a renowned merengue star perform — then a roof collapse killed 124 people
